\title{Centralizer of an element}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-15}
\taxon{definition}

\p{Let #{G} be a [[gr-000G]], let #{a\in G} be an element of the group. We define the \define{Centralizer} of #{a} to be the [[gr-001B]] #{C_{G}(a)} of #{G} whose underlying set equals
##{C_{G}(a)=\{g\in G\mid ag=ga\}.}
Observe this is the same thing as #{C_{G}(a)=C_{G}(\{a\})} the [centralizer](gr-001O) of the singleton #{\{a\}}.}

